By Mr. Mark, a petition (accompanied by bill, Senate, No. 2298) of Paul W. Mark for legislation
to establish standards for cost disclosure at public electric vehicle charging stations.
Telecommunications, Utilities and Energy.
The Commonwealth of Massachusetts
_______________
In the One Hundred and Ninety-Fourth General Court
(2025-2026)
_______________
An Act enabling clean energy transition.
Be it enacted by the Senate and House of Representatives in General Court assembled, and by the authority
of the same, as follows:
1 Section 16 of Chapter 25A of the General Laws as appearing in the 2024 Official Edition
2 is hereby amended by adding at the end after subsection (f) the following subsection:-
3 (g) The executive office of energy and environmental affairs shall promulgate standards
4 and regulations for cost disclosure at all public vehicle charging stations. The owner or operator
5 of a public electric vehicle charging station or a designee shall place at each public charging
6 station where there is a cost to charge, a standardized cost disclosure notice based on the
7 aforementioned standards.
